    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>This small, featureless coin is solid green on one side and solid red on the other.</em></p><p><strong>Effect:</strong> As a maneuver, you toss the coin in the air and let it fall to the ground in front of you. Roll a [[/roll 1d3]] to determine the coin’s effect, depending on which face shows when it lands:</p><ol><li><p><strong>Red:</strong> The area within 2 squares of you is difficult terrain for enemies until the end of your next turn.</p></li><li><p><strong>Green:</strong> You and each ally who starts their turn within 2 squares of you gains a +1 bonus to speed until the end of your next turn. [[/apply BuRuT27XYsyd3Xdq]]</p></li><li><p><strong>Spinning Coin:</strong> Both the red and green effects occur while the coin continuously spins.</p></li></ol><p>The coin must be picked up before it can be used again. If any creature picks up the coin, its effects immediately end.</p>",
